        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 10:57PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1056 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Berryville, moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Dime to Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Coin...                           Carrollton...
Cabanal...                        Urbanette...
Delmar...                         Berryville...
Green Forest...                   Denver...
Connor...                         Rule...
Grandview...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
